description: Schedule A-10 is a demand metered rate schedule for general service customers.  Schedule  A-10 applies to single-phase and polyphase alternating-current service (for a description of these terms, see Section D of Rule 2*).   If the customer's demand exceeds 499 kW for three consecutive months, the customer's account will be transferred to Schedule E-19 or E-20.
name: A-10 Medium General Demand Service (Secondary Voltage)
comments: Fixed Monthly Charge is the Meter Charge Rate per meter per day averaged out for a month. There is also an optional meter data access charge of $0.98563 per meter per day.
